casebody.data:
Robert SCHOMBERGER, Bankrupt, v. NATIONAL MUTUAL SAVINGS ASSOCIATION. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. June 29, 1938. Griffin, Ileal & Emery, of Detroit, Mich., and Frazer & Popkin, of Detroit, Mich., for appellant.

Before HICKS, ALLEN, and HAMILTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It appearing to the court that an appeal was allowed in this case on May 8, 1934, and that no steps have been taken to prosecute appeal since October 3, 1934; it is ordered that the appeal be dismissed.
